Sabre combines a classic aircraft engine with a rocket one. It is designed to propel the aircraft at twice the speed at which the Concorde flew. "Once the Sabre engine is operational, it could allow us to reach Australia in about four hours," said Turnock. And, for example, the distance between London and New York, the plane could manage to travel in one hour.
The server independent notes that the so-called hypersonic flights, in which the speed of sound is exceeded five times, are complicated due to overheating of the engine. But Sabre (Synergetic air Breathing rocket engine) should deal with this problem thanks to the use of super-cold helium, which should prevent the rise in temperatures.
"The most important thing about sabre is that it is a hybrid of a rocket and an aircraft engine that is powered by a stream of exhaust gases created from the air," says Shaun Driscoll of Reaction Engines. "Missiles over the past 70 years have not undergone such a great development, while aircraft ones do. So when you combine the engines, you can have a very light and efficient propulsion system and essentially create a space plane, " he added.
