Prindiš, sparkler and Fišerová safely advanced to the semifinals of the world championship
Kayakers Vít prindiš and Jiří prskavec and canoeist Tereza fišerová safely advanced to the semifinals of the World Cup in water slalom in Seu d'urgell. Prindiš was fourth in Friday's qualifying, sparkler fifth and fišerová eighth. The next three Czech players will be in Spain for the semi-final start in the afternoon qualifying session.
Vavřinec hradilek did not succeed from the strong representative group of kayakers, who immediately at the beginning of the ride received a 50-second penalty for an incorrect passage of the goal. Prindiš and sparkler, on the other hand, can already relax and concentrate on Sunday's semi-final.
"I set myself the goal to go down the first ride to 30, which I managed. Not that I didn't care how I ended up, because Sunday starts very early in the morning, so I was hoping to be a little higher to have a better starting position," said prindiš, praising the well-being in seu. "Before the patrol race, I felt the worst in the 14 days we've been here. Then during the race it was good and today it was better. All the time it's beautiful, nice races, the audience came, so fine, " he smiled.
Even sparkler was happy. "In qualifying, one does not particularly want to make an unnecessary mistake. In the first goals I was not very good. Then I drove the center perfectly, no problems and I knew that I had mileage, so came the second mistake, when I wanted to go down straight and I turned the Erka. Overall, I can not be dissatisfied. The form is, we'll see how it goes from there, " said this year's overall World Cup winner.
Both representatives praised that on Sunday they will go to the start only at the end of the semifinal block. "I'm not a morning person, it's cold in the morning, and when you're here at eight, you want a jacket and a sweatshirt," said prindiš. "Overall, it takes the semifinal an hour and a half, which is a pretty good difference in terms of sleep," sparkler agreed.
Of the trio of Czech singkanoists, only fišerová succeeded, Eva říhová finished two places behind the top 20, Kateřina havlíčková was 35th. "I rode the upper part according to my ideas, in the middle passage it seemed to me that I was not in time and not going according to the plan, but I was able to get to the comfortable track that I wanted to go. I made two putts, and I'm just behind the winner with a clean time. I have a good starting position for the semifinals, " praised fišerová.
