Thank you for the dance! Singer Leonard Cohen will posthumously release the last album
The album "thanks for the dance" will contain unreleased material and various musical collaborations put together by the singer's son. The album comes out 22. November.
In October 2016, the album you want it Darker was released, on which Cohen collaborated with his son Adam. He asked him to help him complete the individual songs. On an intimate recording, Cohen symbolically comes to terms with his impending death. He died a month after the release of the album at the age of 82.
Seven months later, Adam Cohen began to work on the materials left to him by his father. He invited a wide range of musicians to collaborate-Damien Rice, Bryce Dessner, Javier Mase or singer Beck at random.
"When we invented music for my father's words, we used his own characteristic musical techniques. So he's still with us, " said Adam Cohen about the album. "I am most impressed by the reactions of those who have already heard it. One by one they say that Leonard is still alive, " he added.
The first track on the album is a short song called the goal. "I'm almost alive, I'm almost home," Cohen sings in his characteristic honeyed voice. He sang about death, he knew that the release of new material will not live to see. He also admitted this in an interview with the New Yorker magazine a month before his death. "I'm ready to die. I hope it will not be too unpleasant, " he said.
In September 2018, Adam Cohen released a collection of his father's poetry called the flame. In Czech it will be released under the name Plamen 31. December at Argo publishing house.
