Annex 12 / safety rules
1. Definition of terms
1.1. for the purposes of this annex, the following expressions and phrases shall have the meanings set out below:
A security incident means any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of information assets.
Information asset means any information, processes, hardware or software components that (1) support the authorized entity's business activities, or (2) are of value to the authorized entity, or (3) the disclosure, unauthorized modification or unavailability of which has a negative impact on the authorized entity.
Contractor's persons means persons who are directly or indirectly involved in the performance of the subject matter of this contract, including subcontractors of the contractor.
The environment of the authorised entity means the premises in which the authorised entity carries out its business and the information and communication systems used by the authorised entity and containing information assets.
2. Personnel security
2.1 none of the contractor's persons:
2.1.1 does not have a criminal record;
2.1.2. has not been convicted of an intentional crime in the past and is not being prosecuted at the time of performance of the subject matter of this treaty,
2.2 if the contractor finds non-compliance with the above rules in the contractor's persons, he must immediately inform the client thereof. The customer is entitled to demand that such person does not further participate in the implementation of the works arising from the subject matter of this contract, directly or indirectly, and is entitled to demand from the contractor the provision of adequate compensation.
2.3 the contractor shall provide the customer with the full name list of the contractor's persons. The contractor undertakes to inform the customer about changes in the personnel security of the performance of this contract in advance.
2.4 Persons Of The Contractor:
2.4.1. they must be familiar with the following safety rules,
2.4.2 have all the necessary examinations and attestations that result from the law or the regulator's requirements for the type of work they are to perform in connection with the performance of this contract,
2.4.3.they regularly provide training in the field of information security.
2.5.persons of the contractor must not enter the environment of the authorized body under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, combustibles, means of warfare, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substances threatening human life and/or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 access of the contractor's persons to the environment of the authorized body is allowed only if their presence is necessary for the performance of work duties under this contract.
3.2 the contractor's persons always move in the environment of the authorized body accompanied by the responsible employee of the customer.
3.3 the free movement of the contractor's persons in the environment of an authorized body is allowed only if the person has been issued a personal access card. The contractor's person may not further lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties access to the environment of an authorized entity.
3.4 in case of loss of the access card or in case of suspicion of loss of the access card, the contractor is obliged to inform the customer without delay.
3.5 without undue delay after the termination of the works under this agreement or after the termination of this agreement, or if further physical access of the contractor's persons to the environment of an authorized entity is no longer necessary, the client shall ensure that all contractor's persons return the access cards loaned to the client.
3.6 without the prior written consent of the customer, the contractor's person may not remove any information assets from the environment of the authorized entity via a storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of the contractor's persons in the environment of the authorized body
4.1 the contractor's persons are assigned only accounts that allow unambiguous identification of the user and only with such privileges as they absolutely need to perform their professional duties under this agreement.
4.2 the contractor performs routine work under non-privileged accounts, uses accounts with administrative privileges only in necessary cases.
4.3 the contractor's persons may not access the internet if they work under an account with administrative privileges or with applications that are running under administrative privileges.
4.4 inactive accounts of the contractor's persons are proactively reported by the contractor to the customer.
4.5 the contractor uses the shared accounts only with the prior written consent of the customer.
4.6 in case of password disclosure or in case of suspicion of password disclosure, the contractor must immediately ensure that the password is changed or blocked.
5. Handling certificates
5.1 access to certificates (both logical and physical) will be granted only to those persons of the contractor for whom this access is necessary for the performance of their professional duties.
5.2 without the written consent of the customer, the contractor may not provide the certificates or make them available to third parties.
5.3.once installed, certificates may only be stored in a secure location in the places where their storage is necessary for the performance of this Agreement, and any further copies destroyed in a manner that makes it impossible to restore them again.
5.4 if possible, the certificate private key must be set as non-exportable. The private key of the certificate must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in an unencrypted form.
5.5 the contractor undertakes to inform the customer immediately of the loss or suspicion of loss of the confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Management of information assets
6.1 work with information assets is limited only to places that exclude the interception of sensitive information by unauthorized persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with information assets in public transport vehicles, in public places and in places where there is a threat of interception from industrial cameras.
6.2 upon completion of the works arising from this agreement, the contractor shall return or remove without undue delay all information assets stored in the contractor's environment, unless the possession of such information is required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of information assets must be carried out in a way that makes it impossible to restore them again.
6.3 without the prior written consent of the customer, the contractor may not provide access to the information assets to any third parties who are not authorized to participate in the performance of this contract.
6.4 the contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer equipment on which information assets are stored, processed or through which they are transmitted. In relation to Information Assets, The Contractor shall ensure that in the contractor's environment:
6.4.1. tools are used to encrypt disks, folders or files in order to prevent unauthorized access to information assets,
6.4.2. tools for detection and removal of malicious code are used with the setting of Regular updating of the database of malicious code signatures with a frequency not exceeding one week and the corresponding processes of surveillance, logging and response to a positive finding of malicious code are set,
6.4.3 processes for updating security patches of software components are defined, set up, implemented and monitored at intervals not exceeding one month from the release of patches,
6.4.4 the internet environment is separated by a firewall that is connected to the surveillance, and the contractor's persons use an exclusively encrypted VPN connection during remote access, preventing unauthorized interception and modification of transmitted communications.
6.5 if the information assets are transferred by the contractor outside the premises of the authorized body, the contractor is obliged to strictly take care of the physical security of these assets and keep these information assets under constant supervision. The contractor is obliged to comply with the safety and operational instructions of the manufacturer of the hardware on which the information assets are processed.
7. Work in the environment of an authorized body
7.1 the contractor is obliged to get acquainted with and act in accordance with the standard of classification of information assets, if the client provides it to him.
7.2 for hardware that is owned and managed by the customer or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the customer, the contractor may not make unapproved changes to the configuration of this hardware by the customer. In particular, the contractor must not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For any hardware installed in this way, the process for applying security patches, including responsibilities arising from roles within the process, must be explicitly and formally specified.
7.3 without the prior written consent of the customer, the contractor may not install or run any software not previously approved by the customer.
7.4 without the written consent of the customer, the contractor is not entitled to perform any physical or logical safety testing or any type of control mechanisms of the authorized body.
7.5 the contractor shall not tamper with audit records in any way.
7.6 the contractor's persons are not authorized to work with software, hardware or data content that is not directly related to the performance of this agreement.
7.7 contractor persons may not engage in any activity detrimental to other natural or legal persons, including sending unsolicited e-mails, sending fraudulent e-mails, distributing malicious code or engaging in attacks to disable the availability of the services.
7.8 the customer logs all actions performed by the contractor's persons and keeps a record of them for 3 years.
7.9 without the written consent of the customer, the contractor's persons may not connect their own storage devices to any computer equipment of the authorized body.
7.10 at the provided workplace, the contractor's persons are obliged to ensure the following during the period of physical absence::
7.10.1 cleanliness and order so that the workplace can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of All information assets;
7.10.3 logically locking access to information assets so that unauthorized access to such information assets cannot occur.
7.11 without the prior written consent of the customer, the contractor's persons are not entitled to install devices enabling remote interception or to make any audio or video recording.
8. Crisis management
8.1 the contractor's persons are obliged to prevent, as far as possible, the occurrence of emergency situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury or damage to the property of the authorized person could occur.
8.2 in the event of a crisis situation, the contractor's person who is physically present at the site of the event is obliged to comply without exception and without delay with the regulations and directives in force at the site and to obey the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to the case of exercise.
8.3 in case of crisis management, the contractor's person is obliged to follow the instructions of the customer's crisis manager without delay.
9. Reporting of security incidents
9.1 if the contractor identifies a safety incident, it is obliged to report it to the tool without delay https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (telephone: +420 221 710 911).
