The administration of US President Donald Trump is considering revoking permission for Chinese companies to trade on the stock markets in the United States. An informed source told Reuters today. Such a move would be a radical escalation of trade tensions between the US and China. The shares of the companies concerned on the New York Stock Exchange immediately headed down after the news, pulling the entire market with it.
